	<title>Exercises: On Infimum and Supremum</title>
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Suppose <latex>x\in\RNr</latex> satisfies <latex>x\geq 0</latex> and <latex>x\leq 1/10^n</latex> for all <latex>n\geq 1</latex>. Show that <latex>x=0</latex>.</para>
		</problem>
	</exercise>
	
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Show that the set <latex>-\NNr:=\Set{ -n\st n\in \NNr}</latex> is not bounded below.</para>
		</problem>
	</exercise>
	
	<exercise>
		<problem>
			<para>Show that a set <latex>X\subseteq\RNr</latex> is not bounded above if and only if for every <latex>n\in\NNr</latex> there exists <latex>x\in X</latex> with <latex>n\leq x</latex>.</para>
		</problem>
	</exercise>
	
</exercise.pack>